.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE GARLIC-BREAD-2 B "10 Jul 86" 1986
.RZ "SIMPLE GARLIC BREAD" "Quick and easy garlic bread"
This is a quick and painless way to make garlic bread in a hurry.
It might not be a gourmet recipe, but it is easy and tasty.
.IH "serves 4"
.IG "" "butter"
.IG "" "garlic salt"
.IG "" "grated cheese"
.IG "1" "loaf of Italian or French bread"
.PH
.SK 1
Preheat broiler.
Slice loaf of bread lengthwise and butter both halves.
.SK 2
Sprinkle garlic salt and grated cheese on both halves.
.SK 3
Place under broiler until brown (about 3 minutes).
.NX
This also works well with almost any other kind of bread.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
trivial.
.I Time:
3 minutes preparation, 3 minutes cooking.
.I Precision:
no need to measure.
.WR
Dennis Wombough
AT&T Bell Labs, Holmdel, New Jersey
